## Penetration Testing — Before & After

A complete 3-attack penetration test suite demonstrating the security posture before and after implementing 2FA + VPN + ACL.

### How to Run
```bash
# Start the server
python -m uvicorn backend.main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000

# Run the pentest
python attacks/pentest_demo.py
```

### Attack Vectors & Results

| # | Attack | BEFORE Security | AFTER Security | Key Defence |
|---|--------|----------------|---------------|-------------|
| 1 | **Replay Attack** | Captured tokens reused indefinitely | JWT expires (5/30min), TOTP valid 30s only | 2FA + JWT expiry |
| 2 | **Brute-Force Login** | Unlimited attempts, no lockout | Rate-limited at 5/min, locked after 5 fails | Rate limit + lockout + 2FA |
| 3 | **Packet Sniffing** | All data plaintext (passwords, PINs, tokens) | Double encryption (VPN + AES-GCM) | WireGuard + AES-128-GCM |

### Security Controls Summary

| Control | Defends Against |
|---------|----------------|
| Two-Phase Auth (2FA) | Replay, brute-force, credential theft |
| WireGuard VPN | Packet sniffing, MitM, network eavesdropping |
| AES-128-GCM | Payload interception (even inside VPN) |
| Rate Limiting (5/min) | Brute-force, credential stuffing |
| Account Lockout (15min) | Sustained brute-force campaigns |
| JWT Token Expiry | Token replay, session hijacking |
| ACL Middleware | Unauthorized access at network layer |

### File

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| [pentest_demo.py](file:///d:/CN_PROJECT/attacks/pentest_demo.py) | **New** — Full before/after pentest suite (3 attacks) |

